properties.headline: High Wind Watch issued February 4 at 5:08PM MST until February 7 at 5:00AM MST by NWS Salt Lake City UT
properties.description:
* WHAT...West winds gusting in excess of 60 mph possible.

* WHERE...Southwest Wyoming.

* WHEN...Thursday and Thursday night.

* IMPACTS...High winds may cause light unsecured objects to become
airborne. Blowing snow may cause local visibility restrictions
and slick roads. Travel could be difficult especially for high
profile vehicles.
properties.instruction:
Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates on this
situation. Fasten loose objects or shelter objects in a safe
location prior to the onset of winds.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WATCH IN EFFECT FROM LATE WEDNESDAY NIGHT THROUGH LATE THURSDAY NIGHT
